<SampleLayout
	lang="en-US"
	title="Sample how-to guide: Manage API Keys"
	description="Sample how-to guide by Arnaud Hervy demonstrating how to manage API keys in a software platform."
	keywords="technical writing, how-to guide, sample, API keys, instructions, software, documentation"
	canonicalPath="/samples/how-to/"
	ogTitle="Sample how-to guide by Arnaud Hervy: Manage API keys"
	ogDescription="Learn how to create and revoke API keys with clear instructions in this sample how-to guide by Arnaud Hervy."
	ogImage="/assets/how-to.webp"
>
	<h1>Manage API Keys</h1>

	<p>
		Use API keys to authenticate requests to the Llama API. This guide explains how to create and
		revoke API keys safely.
	</p>
	<p>Only Platform Administrators and Platform Owners can manage API keys.</p>

	<h2 id="create-api-key">Create an API Key</h2>

	<p>You can create up to 10 API keys. Each key has the same access rights as your account.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>Go to your <strong>Admin</strong> account.</li>
		<li>In the <strong>Platform settings</strong> section, click <strong>API</strong>.</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Add API key</strong>.</li>
		<li>
			When asked, enter a meaningful label for the API key. For example, indicate which integration
			uses this API key.
		</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Create</strong>.</li>
		<li>Copy your API key and store it securely.</li>
	</ol>

	<div class="alert important">
		You can only view the API key once. If you lose it, you must create a new one.
	</div>

	<ol start="7">
		<li>Click <strong>Close</strong>.</li>
	</ol>

	<h2 id="revoke-api-key">Revoke an API key</h2>
	<p>Revoke an API key if it is no longer needed or if you suspect it has been compromised.</p>
	<p class="alert warning">
		Revoking an API key permanently deletes it. Any integration using this key will stop working
		immediately.
	</p>
	<ol>
		<li>Go to your <strong>Admin</strong> account.</li>
		<li>In the <strong>Platform settings</strong> section, click <strong>API</strong>.</li>
		<li>Find the API key you want to revoke, then click <strong>Revoke</strong>.</li>
		<li>When asked, click <strong>Yes, revoke</strong>.</li>
	</ol>
</SampleLayout>
